    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "Psalms",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 28,
        "summary": "David pleads with the Lord to hear his voice and grant his petitions\u2014David prays, Save Thy people and bless Thine inheritance.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "Unto thee will I cry, O Lord my rock; be not silent to me: lest, if thou be silent to me, I become like them that go down into the pit.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 83:1.",
                        "start": 76,
                        "end": 82
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 88:4; 143:7; Prov. 1:12; 1\u00a0Ne. 14:3; 2\u00a0Ne. 24:15.",
                        "start": 131,
                        "end": 134
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 65,
                        "end": 67
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Hear the voice of my supplications, when I cry unto thee, when I lift up my hands toward thy holy oracle.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 90:4 (1\u20135); 124:39 (38\u201339), 126 (125\u201326).",
                        "start": 98,
                        "end": 104
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Draw me not away with the wicked, and with the workers of iniquity, which speak peace to their neighbours, but mischief is in their hearts.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 26:25.",
                        "start": 74,
                        "end": 79
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Peace.",
                        "start": 80,
                        "end": 85
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Guile; Hypocrisy.",
                        "start": 111,
                        "end": 119
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 120,
                        "end": 122
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Give them according to their deeds, and according to the wickedness of their endeavours: give them after the work of their hands; render to them their desert.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Good Works.",
                        "start": 29,
                        "end": 34
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "OR\u00a0due reward.",
                        "start": 151,
                        "end": 157
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Because they regard not the works of the Lord, nor the operation of his hands, he shall destroy them, and not build them up.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 5:12 (11\u201312).",
                        "start": 28,
                        "end": 33
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Blessed be the Lord, because he hath heard the voice of my supplications.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 8,
                        "end": 10
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The Lord is my strength and my shield; my heart trusted in him, and I am helped: therefore my heart greatly rejoiceth; and with my song will I praise him.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Faith.",
                        "start": 48,
                        "end": 55
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 9,
                        "end": 11
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The Lord is their strength, and he is the saving strength of his anointed.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 9,
                        "end": 11
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 35,
                        "end": 37
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Save thy people, and bless thine inheritance: feed them also, and lift them up for ever.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            }
        ]
    }
}